  "prompt": "Do employees at Merge Health Care have a good work-life balance? Does this differ across positions and departments?",
  "response": "I don't have access to real-time data or specific employee experiences at Merge Health Care, but work-life balance can vary widely within any organization based on several factors, including the department, position, management practices, and company culture.\n\nGenerally, employees in roles with more flexible schedules or remote work options may report a better work-life balance. Conversely, positions that demand high levels of responsibility or have tight deadlines may experience more challenges in achieving that balance. \n\nTo get a clearer picture of work-life balance at Merge Health Care, it may be helpful to look at employee reviews on platforms like Glassdoor or Indeed, or to reach out to current or former employees for their insights. Additionally, company policies related to work hours, leave, and remote working practices can give you an idea of how the organization supports work-life balance across different roles and departments.",
